\item \strong{Nearest-centroid} (\code{\link[=getlocspointibss]{getlocspointibss()}}, \code{\link[=getlocspointiss]{getlocspointiss()}}): always
assigns the closest polygon centroid — useful as a fallback when GPS
positions sit just outside a polygon boundary.
}

